						               													<description>From the instructions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;PerPlexus is a game requiring both quick thinking and a constantly changing strategy.  The play board is a network comprised of 6 sliding play pieces or shuttles that can be moved right or left, offensively or defensively, by either player.  The game objective is to place 5 stones in a row -- horizontally, vertically, or diagonally -- while blocking the opponent's attempts to line up 6 stones in a row.  Each shuttle has spaces for 7 stones.  PerPlexus requires that a player plan moves several turns in advance whether playing stones or moving shuttles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
